<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Talks With China Focus on Force Reduction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Talks With China Focus on Force Reduction </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304091494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The two-day meeting of the Indo-China border expert 
group concluded in Beijing yesterday. It discussed among other 
things reduction of forces along the Line of Actual Control and 
other confidence building measures. The experts panel is part 
of the Indo-China Joint Working Group, JWG, which was set up in 
1988. The JWG is scheduled to hold its next meeting in Beijing 
in the middle of the year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

