<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Satisfaction Expressed Over PRC Border Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satisfaction Expressed Over PRC Border Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304153694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304153694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India and China have discussed further measures for 
the maintenance of peace and tranquility along the Line of 
Control and border areas. During the two-day meeting of 
India-China experts group which concluded in Beijing yesterday, 
the two countries expressed satisfaction at the peaceful 
situation on the Line of Actual Control following the 
confidence-building measures initiated by the two countries. 
The two sides reached an agreement on the work regulations of 
the experts group spelling out the mandate, tasks, and 
modalities to be followed. The document was signed yesterday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

