<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Chairs Offense Control Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhu Rongji Chairs Offense Control Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204092094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0732 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2204092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 22 Apr (XINHUA) -- Acting Premier Zhu 
Rongji today chaired the State Council's 18th executive meeting 
to discuss the additional regulations (draft) for the "PRC 
Regulations Governing Offenses Against Public Order." The 
meeting later adopted, in principle, the draft additional 
regulations. 
  The meeting maintained that, since they came into effect on 
1 
January 1987, the current regulations have played a significant 
role in safeguarding social order and social stability. 
However, with the development of the economy and the deepening 
of reform and opening up, many new situtions and new issues with 
regard to public order have appeared. Thus, the additional 
regulations are very essential for strengthening control over 
public offense; safeguarding public order, safety, and 
interests; and protecting citizens' legitimate rights and 
interests so that reform, opening up, and socialist 
modernization can proceed smoothly. 
  The meeting adopted, in principle, the additional 
regulations 
(draft), which the State Council will submit to the National 
People's Congress Standing Committee after further revision. 

</TEXT>

