<H3> <TI>   Tian Jiyun Inspects Langfang Development Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tian Jiyun Inspects Langfang Development Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204080094 Shijiazhuang HEBEI RIBAO in Chinese 9 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Shijiazhuang HEBEI RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Zhao Zhensheng (6392 2182 5116), Wang Chongyu </F>
(3769 1504 3768), and Liu Jing (0491 2533): "Unswervingly 
Develop Township Enterprises"] 
  [Text] On 7 April, accompanied by Li Bingliang, deputy 
secretary of the provincial party committee; Gao Yongtang, vice 
chairman of the provincial people's congress standing committee; 
and responsible comrades of the Langfang city party committee 
and government; Tian Jiyun, member of the Political Bureau of 
the CPC Central Committee and vice chairman of the National 
People's Congress Standing Committee, successively inspected 
Langfang Economic and Technological Development Zone and rural 
areas in Anci District. 
  During the inspection tour, Tian Jiyun listened to work 
briefings given by the Langfang city party committee and the 
city government. On hearing that the output value of Langfang 
city's township enterprises totalled 17.72 billion yuan which 
accounted for 70 percent of the total industrial output value, 
Tian Jiyun said: Developing township enterprises is where the 
hope of making peasants attain a better-off level of moderate 
prosperity lies. Without the great development of township 
enterprises, there can be no rural modernization, and without 
rural modernization, there can be no national modernization. 
Therefore, no matter under what circumstances, we should 
unswervingly develop township enterprises in the course of 
developing the rural economy. Certainly, it is hard to avoid 
some problems in the process of developing township enterprises, 
namely, pollution and low efficiency problems. However, we 
should not negate it because of the existence of some problems 
which must be solved in the course of development. We should 
proceed from the fundamental interests of the state and from the 
interests of peasants, and never slightly waver in our 
determination to develop township enterprises. 
  Tian Jiyun pointed out: Langfang is surrounded by Beijing 
and Tianjin. To accelerate the pace of economic development, we 
must take advantage of its location of being surrounded by 
Beijing and Tianjin to seize the two major markets of Beijing 
and Tianjin and try by all possible means to render good service 
and to seek development and economic efficiency in the course of 
giving 

</TEXT>

