<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    NATO Threatens Serbs With Air Strikes </H4>

<F P=102> OW2204191694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1802 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] London, April 22 (XINHUA) -- NATO today threatened 
the use of air power against the Bosnian Serb Forces around the 
Muslim town of Gorazde unless they pull back three kilometers 
from the center of the town by 00:01 GMT on Sunday [24 April], 
according to the BBC. 
  The ultimatum, issued after a meeting of NATO ambassadors at 
the NATO headquarters in Brussels, also asked Serbs to stop 
shelling Gorazde immediately and give U.N. personnel access to 
the town, one of the six U.N.-designated "safe areas" for 
Muslims in Bosnia. 
  NATO said that if all conditions were not met, it would 
consider air strikes on Serb positions within a 20-kilometer 
radius of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

