<H4>    NATO Gives Serbs Ultimatum on Gorazde </H4>

<F P=102> OW2304011694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0057 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304011694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 22 (XINHUA) -- The North Atlantic 
Treaty Organization (NATO) issued an ultimatum here today to the 
Bosnian Serbs to stop their shelling of the besieged Muslim 
enclave of Gorazde or face air strikes. 
  A NATO statement said that the Serbs must agree to an 
immediate cease-fire and withdraw their forces three kilometers 
from the center of the city of Gorazde or risk allied air raids 
as early as 0001 GMT Sunday. 

</TEXT>

