<H4>    Kozyrev Urges Meeting Obligations </H4>

<F P=102> OW2304182894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1647 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 23 (XINHUA) -- Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev today urged Bosnian Serbs to carry out 
their own obligations, describing this as the only alternative 
before the planned NATO air strikes. 
  In an interview with the INTERFAX NEWS AGENCY, the Russian 
minister stressed that the decision, made by the North Atlantic 
Treaty Organization (NATO) Thursday [21 April] on imposing 
ultimatum on Bosnian Serbs, accords with the U.N. demands. 
  He said that the military leadership of the Bosnian Serbs 
has 
thrown down an criminal gauntlet to elementary norms of 
humanity, demands of the U.N. Security Council and Russia. 
  However, Kozyrev pointed out that NATO should coordinate 
with 
U.N. Peacekeeping Forces and should not overstep the limits of 
the tasks aimed at protecting security in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

