<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Bosnian Serbs Agree To Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> OW2304224594 Beijing XINHUA in English 2154 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 23 (XINHUA) -- A cease-fire 
agreement has been reached today between the U.N. secretary- 
general's special representative for the former Yugoslavia and 
Bosnian Serb civilian and military authorities. 
  According to the agreement, which is available here, both 
sides have agreed on "an immediate and total cease-fire in and 
around Gorazde from 1200 hours" on Saturday [23 April] and 
immediate start of negotiations on all military matters. 
  They also agreed on, as a first step, urgent deployment of a 
U.N. Protection Force (Unprofor) battalion in an area of three 
kilometers from the center of Gorazde on both sides of the Drina 
River, from which Bosnian Serb Forces will be redeployed by 
midnight on Saturday, to closely monitor, supervise and report 
on the observance of the cease-fire by both parties. 
  Not later than midnight on April 26, heavy weapons will be 
withdrawn out of a 20 kilometer radius of the center of Gorazde 
and out of range so as not to constitute a threat to the safe 
area, the agreement said. 
  The two sides also agreed on the guarantee of secure 
conditions for immediate medical evacuation from Gorazde and 
complete freedom of movement for all personnel of Unprofor and 
humanitarian organizations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

