<H4>    UN Warns of Air Strike Following Deadline </H4>

<F P=102> OW2304224694 Beijing XINHUA in English 2207 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304224694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 23 (XINHUA) -- U.N. 
Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali will immediately authorize 
the use of NATO air strikes against Bosnian Serb Forces if they 
do not withdraw from a 3-kilometer zone from the center of 
Gorazde by midnight. 
  "Should the required cease-fire and withdrawal fail to take 
place by 0001 hours GMT April 24, the secretary-general will 
immediately authorize the use of air strikes to protect the safe 
area of Gorazde," Joe Sills, spokesman for the 
secretary-general, said here this evening. 

