<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kozyrev, Christopher To Discuss Bosnia </H4>

<F P=102> OW2604003594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1841 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604003594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 25 (XINHUA) -- Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev and U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher have agreed to meet for talks on Bosnian settlement 
in Geneva on Tuesday [26 April], the Russian Foreign Ministry 
announced today. 
  At their working meeting, the two ministers will discuss 
urgent issues of mutual concern, including the implementation of 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin's proposal to hold a high-level 
meeting to discuss Bosnian settlement with the participation of 
Russia, the United States, the European Union and the United 
Nations. 
  Moreover, Kozyrev and Christopher also plan to consult some 
European powers and, if the need arises, representatives of the 
warring sides in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In a statement issued earlier on Monday, the ministry said 
that "active work of the special envoys to the former Yugoslavia 
and the foreign ministers of Russia, the United States and the 
European Union with the participation of the United Nations" 
must provide the basis for an upcoming high-level meeting on 
Bosnian solution. 
  "We expect that the Bosnian sides and our partners in the 
settlement process will take an active part," the ministry said. 
It stressed that "despite the complexity of the situation, 
military measures must not overshadow the line for a political 
settlement." 

</TEXT>

