<H3> <TI>   Albania Ratifies NATO's Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Albania Ratifies NATO's Partnership for Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304194794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1627 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 23 (XINHUA) -- The Albanian parliament 
today ratified a document on Partnership for Peace with NATO as 
a step toward better relations with West European countries. 
  In February, Albanian President Sali Berisha signed the 
document with NATO Secretary General Manfred Worner in Brussels 
and later submitted it to the People's Assembly for approval. 
  Before the parliament convened over the weekend, the 
president told the lawmakers that ratification of the agreement 
was an important step toward new cooperation with NATO. 
  He stressed that it was also part of Albania's efforts to 
obtain full membership in NATO. 
  The document provides that Albania and NATO will cooperate 
in 
peacekeeping missions, rescue operations and military exercises. 
  No further details were available. 

</TEXT>

