<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng, Nazarbayev Sign Border Treaty in Almaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng, Nazarbayev Sign Border Treaty in Almaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604093994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0902 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Almaty, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Chinese 
Premier Li Peng and Kazakhstan President N.A. Nazarbayev signed 
a border agreement between the two countries here today. 
  After the signing ceremony, Li called the agreement "a 
historic document," which defines the over-1,700-kilometer-long 
border between the two countries in a legal form. 
  This, he said, would serve to boost the development of the 
existing bilateral relations of friendship. 
  Nazarbayev said the agreement symbolizes a long-term good- 
neighborly relationship between the two countries. 
  He expected the Sino-Kazakhstan border to be one of peace 
and 
friendship. 
  Also signed were an agreement on China providing loans to 
Kazakhstan, notes to be exchanged on China presenting a batch of 
materials to Kazakhstan, and a summary of talks on developing 
international railway transportation between the Chinese 
Ministry of Railways and Kazakhstan's Ministry of Communications. 

</TEXT>

