<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CPPCC Official, Jordan's Upper House Speaker Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CPPCC Official, Jordan's Upper House Speaker Hold Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2404162994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1553 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2404162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, April 24 (XINHUA) -- A 10-member delegation 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
(CPPCC) arrived here today on a four-day visit to the Kingdom to 
promote bilateral relations. 
  The delegation is headed by Wang Zhaoguo, vice chairman of 
the CPPCC. 
  Soon after his arrival, Wang Zhaoguo headed for the 
Jordanian 
parliament to meet with Senate Speaker Ahmed al-Lawzi. 
  In his speech at the meeting, al-Lawzi said that the sphere 
of cooperation between Jordan and China is vast, including 
domains of politics, economy, culture, trade, youth and sports. 
  He lauded China's stand on supporting the just causes in the 
Inzmnal arena. Saying that China is of significance in the on 
going Middle East peace process and a foundation on which Jordan 
relies. 
  He noted that it is important for Jordan that China is one 
of 
the five permanent U.N. Security Council members. He called for 
Chinese action to help implement relevant U.N. resolutions on 
the Arab-Israeli conflict and on the Middle East peace issue. 
  Al-Lawzi also asked the Chinese side to import phosphate, 
potash and chemical fertilizers from Jordan to address the 
current trade imbalance between the two countries. 
  In his speech, Wang Zhaoguo introduced to his Jordanian 
hosts 
the achievements China has made during the past 15 years of 
reform and economic construction. 
  Wang spoke highly of Jordan's peaceful, neutral and 
non-aligned foreign policy, saying that the Kingdom has made 
unswerving efforts for the Arab-Israeli peace talks and the 
Middle East peace process. 
  He said that China is devoted to developing friendly ties 
with all countries, especially the developing countries no 
matter how the international situation changes, Wang said, 
China's principled stand of peaceful co-existence and the policy 
of developing friendly and cooperative relations with developing 
countries will not change. 
  Wang said China has consistently supported the just struggle 
of the Palestinian people, advocating a political solution to 
the Middle East problem on the basis of relevant U.N. 
resolutions, especially on U.N. Security Council Resolution MWRW 
[as received] and 338. 
  On behalf of the CPPCC, Wang extended an invitation to 
al-Lawzi for a visit to China next year, and al-Lawzi accepted 
the invitation. 
  He is expected to meet with Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali later today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-3885 </DOCNO>
