<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lhasa's Potala Palace To Install Security System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lhasa's Potala Palace To Install Security System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2604060494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 0652 GMT 
5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2604060494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Zhu Daian (2612 0108 1344): "Advanced </F>
Security System To Be Installed in Potala Palace"] 
  [Text] Lhasa, 5 Apr (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--A responsible 
official from the office in charge of repairing Potala Palace 
said in an interview that the installation of a security system 
using modern safety technology had begun recently. 
  Potala Palace, which was built more than 1,000 years ago, is 
famous as the palace at the highest altitude in the world. 
Being the crystallization of the wisdom of the Tibetan people 
and the gem of Chinese culture, Potala Palace is the key object 
of protection by the state and the Tibet Autonomous Region. 
  The safety technology and the security project is a new item 
in Potala Palace's full-scale repair and maintenance project, 
which has been going on for the last five years. The project 
includes an automatic system to fight fires, an automatic 
burglar detection system, a television monitoring system, and a 
command and communications system. The equipment is all 
technologically advanced by international standards. After the 
completion of the project, the screens in the control center 
will show the safety conditions throughout the palace, and the 
systems will perform the automatic fire fighting and burglar 
detection functions. 
  It has been learned that the safety and protection project 
in 
Potala Palace is costing approximately 3 million yuan, and it is 
expected that it will be officially put into operation in early 
August. 

</TEXT>

