<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Reportedly Grants Asylum to Escaped Dissident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Reportedly Grants Asylum to Escaped Dissident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2404050894 Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO in Chinese 24 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK2404050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By special reporter Shi Lei (4258 4320): "Democratic </F>
Activist Wang Jiaqi Fled to Hong Kong and Is Granted Political 
Asylum by the United States"] 
  [Text] Democratic activist Wang Jiaqi, who has fled from 
Mainland China to Hong Kong, will go to the United States in the 
near future after a brief stay in Hong Kong. It is said that 
the U.S. Government has already approved Wang Jiaqi's request 
and granted him political asylum. 
  An informed source said the department concerned of the Hong 
Kong Government had a contact with Wang Jiaqi last week and 
asked him to keep a low profile during his stay in Hong Kong. 
Wang agreed to do so. 
  It is said that Wang Jiaqi is now staying on Lamma Island in 
Hong Kong, and he is maintaining contact with the outside 
through a non-government organization. 
  The Mainland Chinese government is quite concerned about 
possible leakage of secrets due to Wang Jiaqi's flight, and 
Mainland Chinese agencies in Hong Kong are busy in detecting 
Wang Jiaqi's move. 

</TEXT>

