<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provisional Rules on Import Registration, Quotas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Provisional Rules on Import Registration, Quotas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2304080294 Beijing CHINA DAILY in English 23 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK2304080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing CHINA DAILY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [CD News: Easier Steps for Imports] </F>
  [Text] China yesterday issued two provisional regulations 
on the automatic registration of specific product imports and 
the management of product import quotas. 
  The two regulations were jointly announced by the State 
Planning Commission, the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic 
Co-operation, People's Bank of China, the State General 
Administration of Customs and the State Administration of 
Exchange Control. 
  The move is to ensure the smooth implementation of the 
reform 
of foreign exchange management and to provide the information 
needed to strengthen macro-economic supervision over major 
product imports. 
  According to the new regulations, automatic registration 
will 
be in place for such products as rolled steel, billet, scrap 
steel, used ships, nonferrous metals (copper and aluminium), 
plastics materials, paper, fruits, and cosmetics. 
  Under the regulations, the procedures for import 
registration 
should be followed for categories including general-import 
trade, imports based on foreign government or bank loans, mail 
imports and leasing imports. 

</TEXT>

