<H3> <TI>   Anhui Provincial People's Congress Meets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anhui Provincial People's Congress Meets </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Approves Economic, Social Development Plan </H4>

<F P=102> OW2504130994 Hefei ANHUI RIBAO in Chinese 13 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> OW2504130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hefei ANHUI RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Resolution of the Second Session of the Eighth Anhui </F>
Provincial People's Congress on the Implementation of the 1993 
Provincial Economic and Social Development Plan and the Plan for 
1994 Adopted by the Second Session of the Eighth Anhui 
Provincial People's Congress on 12 April 1994"] 
  [Text] Through examination and after consulting the 
Examination Committees' report on the provincial economic and 
social development plan as well as fiscal budget, the Second 
Session of the Eighth Anhui Provincial People's Congress has 
decided to approve the 1994 Anhui provincial economic and social 
development plan and also the "Report on the Implementation of 
the 1993 Anhui Provincial Economic and Social Development Plan 
and the Draft Plan for 1994" made by Chairman Huang Yuezhong of 
the provincial Planning Commission. 
  This is a crucial year for promoting reform in an all-round 
manner and for accelerating the establishment of a socialist 
market economic structure. Following the guidelines of the 
Second Session of the Eighth Anhui Provincial People's Congress, 
governments at various levels should have a good grasp of the 
relations between reform, development, and stability; should 
further deepen various reforms; should strengthen and improve 
macrocontrol; should strictly control the increase of commodity 
prices; should show actual concern for the living condition of 
the masses; and should promote a sustained, rapid, and sound 
development of the national economy. It is necessary to place 
the development of agriculture first; promote all-round 
development of the rural economy; increase the peasants' income; 
vigorously promote the establishment of a modern enterprise 
system; improve the economic structure; quicken technological 
progress; strengthen operations and management; increase 
economic efficiency; effectively improve the investment 
structure; attach importance to building key projects; open up 
wider to the outside world; and seriously attach importance to 
education, science, and technological work. Governments at 
various levels throughout the entire province must improve their 
style, struggle in unity, and mobilize and rely on the masses to 
fulfill the 1994 economic and social development plan in an 
all-round manner. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

