<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Holds Provincial Reform Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shandong Holds Provincial Reform Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604021894 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2604021894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The provincial meeting on the work of opening to 
the outside world was held in Jinan on 25 April. Under the 
guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics and the guidelines of the 14th 
party congress and of the third plenary session of the 14th CPC 
Central Committee, participants in this meeting conscientiously 
summarized the province's opening up work since the commencement 
of reform and opening up since 1992. In particular, they 
learned from and used for reference the successful experiences 
of fraternal provinces and municipalities, researched and drew 
up the province's general pattern of opening up in the 
foreseeable future, and defined the province's overall goal and 
policy on developing the economy oriented to opening up in the 
next step. Attending the meeting were provincial leading 
comrades Jiang Chunyun, Zhao Zhihao, Li Chunting, Li Wenquan, Li 
Zhen, and Lu Maozeng. Li Chunting presided over the meeting. 
  He said: This meeting, held by the provincial party 
committee and the provincial government, is an important one 
related to the province's overall economic situation and is a 
major move adopted by the province to accelerate the development 
of the economy oriented to opening up since the issuance of Deng 
Xiaoping's speeches made during his south China trip in spring 
of 1992 and since the convocation of the provincial meeting on 
opening up. The purpose of this meeting is to again mobilize 
the whole province to deepen reform and open even wider to the 
outside world and to further emancipate the mind and seek unity 
in understanding and action in order to push the province's 
opening up towards the orientation of high level, high sphere, 
and in-depth development. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

