<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Company Invents Deep-Sea Fibre Optics Cables </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shandong Company Invents Deep-Sea Fibre Optics Cables </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504150694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 2103 
GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2504150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondents Li Xudong (2621 2485 2639) and Jiang </F>
Anjian (5592 1344 0256)] 
  [Text] Jinan, 3 Apr (XINHUA) -- The Zaozhuang Hengli 
Optics Communications Company in Shandong successfully invented 
our country's first deep-sea fibre optics cable and filled in 
the production gaps in our country's optics communications 
material. 
  Deep-sea fibre optics cable is a kind of fibre optics 
communications cable laid on seabeds. Such cables must be 
highly resistant to water and corrosion, and must be able to 
withstand heavy pounding from the sea. So far such cables are 
only produced by a handful of developed countries such as the 
United States, Germany, and Britain. Our successful invention 
was the result of joint research begun last May by the Zaozhuang 
Hengli Optics Communications Company and the No.8 Research 
Center affiliated to the Ministry of Electronics Industry. 
Tests conducted by fibre optics communications research and 
monitoring centers in Guangzhou, Shanghai, Wuxi, and other 
localities have proved that the cable's performance has reached 
or surpassed similar products produced abroad. Batch production 
of the cables has begun. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

