<H3> <TI>   Mobile Phone Production Line Begins in Zhejiang's Hangzhou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mobile Phone Production Line Begins in Zhejiang's Hangzhou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504133394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1259 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2504133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, April 25 (XINHUA) -- A modern mobile 
telephone production line started operating early this month in 
Hangzhou in east China's Zhejiang Province. 
  It is expected to produce the world's up-to-date 9900X 
mobile 
phones for this country's large telecommunications market. 
  With an annual production capacity of 400,000 mini mobile 
phones, the production line is another important landmark for 
Hangzhou Telecommunications Equipment Factory, which last April 
put into operation an 8900X production line, using technology 
from Motorola, the U.S. blue-chip company. 
  According to sources from the Ministry of Posts and 
Telecommunications, China has registered 480,000 subscribers of 
mobile telephones, 2.67 times the total figure for all the 
previous years. 

</TEXT>

