<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Building Materials Industry Thrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing Building Materials Industry Thrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504124494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1201 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2504124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 25 (XINHUA)--Building materials have 
become the third biggest industry of Beijing, after the 
automotive and electronics industries. 
  Officials of the Beijing Urban and Rural Construction 
Committee said that the industry had a turnover of 7.5 billion 
yuan and exports worth 31.33 million U.S. dollars in 1993. 
  A large part of the value was created in modern building 
materials, such as cement, new wall material, sound-proof, fire- 
proof and water-proof materials, porcelain ware, decoration 
materials and hardware, rather than in bricks, sand and other 
traditional products, the officials said. 
  According to the officials, energy-saving and other 
high-tech 
new building materials will be the direction for future 
development. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

