<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sichuan Province Reportedly To Sell State Firms to Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sichuan Province Reportedly To Sell State Firms to Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604062794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0550 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604062794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, April 26 KYODO -- The Chinese Province of 
Sichuan has decided to sell 33 national enterprises with good 
business performance to overseas bidders, according to a CHINA 
NEWS SERVICE report. 
  The news agency said the corporations to be sold to bolster 
them with foreign capital include large-scale firms and belong 
to various industries such as machinery, electronics, metallurgy 
and pharmaceuticals. 
  The 33 companies, with a combined workforce of 77,000, hold 
fixed assets worth 3.6 billion yuan (about 43 billion yen), the 
agency said. 
  Foreign bidders will be allowed to purchase them outright, 
partially or through acquisition of equity shares, the agency 
said. 
  Provincial authorities offered 16 deficit-ridden enterprises 
for sale to Hong Kong bidders last year but none was purchased. 

</TEXT>

