<H3> <TI>   Ministry Notes Amount of Narcotics Seized in 1st Quarter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Notes Amount of Narcotics Seized in 1st Quarter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604095794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0927 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 26 (XINHUA) -- China's public 
security bodies have cracked more than 2,000 cases of narcotics 
trafficking during the first quarter of this year, seizing 
2,000-plus kilograms of various drugs. 
  Officials from the Ministry of Public Security said that 
public security departments in Yunnan, Guangxi, Fujian and 
Guangdong Provinces, which are located in south-western border 
areas and in south-eastern coastal areas, have strengthened 
border and coast defences and speeded up investigations. 
  During the first three months, Yunnan Province successfully 
dealt with about 900 cases of drug-trafficking, and seized over 
700 kilograms of narcotics. 
  The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and Guangdong Province 
each cleared up 400 such cases in that period. 
  Fujian Province cracked 22 cases, and seized about 40 
kilograms of various drugs. 57 criminals were caught in the 
province, some of whom came from Taiwan province. 
  Big drug-trafficking cases were also cleared up in Shaanxi, 
Gansu, Qinghai, Henan, Hunan, Shandong and Sichuan provinces and 
in Beijing. 
  Officials said that local people have played a very 
important 
role in the anti-drug campaign. 

</TEXT>

