<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Secretary Meets With Hong Kong Businessman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong Secretary Meets With Hong Kong Businessman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2604081894 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2604081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday afternoon, Xie Fei, member of the 
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and secretary of 
the Guangdong Provincial CPC Committee, met with Mr. Lee 
Shau-kee, Hong Kong affairs adviser and president of Hong Kong 
Henderson Investment Ltd., in Guangzhou's Zhudao Guesthouse. 
  Xie Fei appreciated the action of loving China, Hong Kong 
and 
one's native place of Hong Kong Henderson Investment Ltd. in 
actively participating in China's economic construction, 
donating funds to run schools, and training various kinds of 
management personnel for China. He added: As long as the 
inland economy develops well, Hong Kong will achieve greater 
development. Both sides can thus give full play to their own 
strong points. 
  Xie Fei also urged the accompanying responsible persons of 
Guangzhou City to pay attention to formulating plans well to 
integrate in a still better way the transformation of the old 
urban area with the adjustment of the distribution of industry 
to speed up the pace of transforming the old urban area. Mr. 
Lee Shau-kee and his party came to Guangzhou to discuss with the 
city authorities the second phase of investment and cooperative 
projects, including transformation and expansion of Guangzhou 
Oil Gas Plant, and others. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

