<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Amendment `Absolutely Unacceptable' </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804091294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0903 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 28 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Foreign 
Ministry spokesman said here today that the modified Murkowski 
Amendment is absolutely unacceptable and urged the U.S. 
Government to abide by the principles of the three Sino-U.S. 
Communiques and take effective measures to keep the Sino-U.S 
relations from serious harm. 
  The modified Murkowski Amendment adopted by the joint 
conference of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the 
U.S. on April 19, asserts that the Taiwan Relations Act takes 
primacy over the Sino-U.S. August 17 Joint Communique. 
  The spokesman, Wu Jianmin, said that the Murkowski 
Amendment, 
which asserts that sections 2 and 3 of the Taiwan Relations Act 
take primacy over statements of U.S. policy, including 
communiques, regulations, directives and policies based thereon, 
is designed, in essence, to negate the Sino-U.S. August 17 
Joint Communique, undermine Sino-U.S. relations and erect 
obstacles to the great cause of the peaceful reunification of 
the Chinese people. 
  It is absolutely unacceptable and the Chinese Government and 
people are firmly against it, Wu said. 
  "We demand that the U.S. Government take this case 
seriously, abide by the guiding principles of the Sino-U.S. 
relations as set forth in their three joint communiques, live 
up to its promises and take effective measures immediately to 
keep the Sino-U.S. relations from serious harm," Wu said. 

</TEXT>

