<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Emphasizes Hong Kong Development </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804101294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1004 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 28 (XINHUA) -- China will continue to 
make efforts to promote Hong Kong's economic development and 
improve people's living there, Wu jianmin, Chinese Foreign 
Ministry spokesman, said here today. 
  He told a weekly news briefing here this afternoon that the 
two panels of the Preliminary Working Committee (PWC) for the 
Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative 
Region in charge of political and economic affairs will meet in 
Hong Kong from May 2-3 and from May 4-5, respectively. 
  Lu Ping, PWC deputy director and secretary-general, will 
head 
mainland members of the two panels and other personnel of the 
PWC Secretariat to attend the meetings in Hong Kong, he said. 
  While in Hong Kong, Lu will listen to advice and proposals 
from the Hong Kong people, he said. 
  "The Chinese side has always been greatly concerned with the 
economic affairs and people's livelihood of Hong Kong," he 
noted. "We have already made efforts, and will continue to do 
so, in order to promote Hong Kong's economic prosperity and 
improve the people's livelihood there," he stated. 
  He said that China hopes to maintain cooperative relations 
with the British side in this regard. 
  Whether or not the cooperation will go smoothly depends 
entirely on the attitude and actions of the British side, Wu 
added. 

</TEXT>

