<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi, Canada's Hnatyshyn Discuss Friendship, Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qiao Shi, Canada's Hnatyshyn Discuss Friendship, Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604153394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1500 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Chairman Qiao Shi of 
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) 
and visiting Canadian Governor General Ramon John Hnatyshyn had 
an hour- long discussion on furthering Sino-Canadian friendship 
and cooperation here today. 
  Qiao said that Hnatyshyn's visit provides a good opportunity 
as well as a forceful push for the deepening of the traditional 
relations between the two countries. 
  Hnatyshyn told Qiao that he has had fruitful talks with 
President Jiang Zemin and acting Premier Zhu Rongji since his 
arrival yesterday. 
  China's highly successful economic reform has won the 
Canadian people's admiration and praise, he said, adding that 
Canada has great interests in expanding cooperation with China. 
  Qiao briefed the visitor on the NPC's efforts in improving 
the legal system for a socialist market economy in China. 
  Qiao said that in its law-making process, the NPC has drawn 
experience from other countries. 
  He stressed that to continue to expand Sino-Canadian 
cooperation in various fields is not only the common desire of 
the two sides but is also very promising because conditions are 
available. China is ready to work towards this end, he added. 
  Qiao and Hnatyshyn agreed that the NPC and the Canadian 
Parliament should have more exchanges with a view to deepening 
understanding and promoting cooperation. 
  After the meeting, Hnatyshyn was escorted on a brief tour of 
the Great Hall of the People, which is the seat of the NPC. 

</TEXT>

