<H3> <TI>   Premier Li Peng Visits Kazakhstan 26 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Premier Li Peng Visits Kazakhstan 26 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Li Peng Attends Banquet </H4>

<F P=102> OW2604171494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1620 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alma-Ata [Almaty], April 26 (XINHUA) -- Kazakhstan 
President N.A. Nazarbayev said today that his country will 
develop a long-term and stable relationship of cooperation with 
China. 
  The president hosted a grand banquet here this evening to 
welcome Chinese Premier Li Peng on his official visit to 
Kazakhstan. 
  Nazarbayev, calling Kazakhstan a bridge between the East and 
West, said the people of Kazakhstan know well China's long 
history and industrious people. 
  The Government of Kazakhstan appreciates China's important 
role in the world and its principles for handling international 
relations, he said. 
  Li Peng, referring to his talks with Nazarbayev held this 
morning, said they discussed a wide range of issues in an 
in-depth manner. 
  President Nazarbayev's remarks on Kazakhstan attaching 
importance to developing relations with China left a deep 
impression on him, Li said. 
  Li voiced again his appreciation for Kazakhstan's position 
on 
opposing national splittism, adhering to the "One China" policy 
as well as on the Tibet issue. 
  China appreciates President Nazarbayev's efforts to promote 
peace and stability in Asia, he said. 
  Today, China and Kazakhstan face the common task of building 
a new "Silk Road," which should be fully used to seek common 
prosperity and development, he said. 

</TEXT>

