<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Announces Plan for `High-Level' Talks With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Announces Plan for `High-Level' Talks With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704151794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1502 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alma-ata [Almaty], April 27 (XINHUA) -- Visiting 
Chinese Premier Li Peng said today that there will be high-level 
exchange of visits between Chinese and Russian leaders this year. 
  The Chinese premier made the announcement at a press 
conference here this afternoon, a day before ending his tour of 
Central Asia. 
  Asked about Sino-Russian relations, Li called the growth of 
such ties normal in the past few years. 
  President Boris Yeltsin paid a fruitful visit to China and 
bilateral trade has surpassed the level of that with the former 
Soviet Union, Li said. 
  Touching on the so-called China's intention to "fill in the 
vacuum" left by the disintegration of the former Soviet Union, 
Li restated that China seeks no spheres of influence, neither 
political or economic, in Central Asia. 
  "We have a lot of matters to take care of at home and have 
no 
interest or intention to fill in the so-called vacuum," Li said. 
  His visit is meant to develop friendship with the Central 
Asian nations and not directed against any other countries, Li 
said. 

</TEXT>

