<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Holds 2d Talks With Kazakhstan's Nazarbayev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Holds 2d Talks With Kazakhstan's Nazarbayev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704155994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1547 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alma-ata [Almaty], April 27 (XINHUA) -- Visiting 
Chinese Premier Li Peng today met again Kazakhstan President N. 
A. Nazarbayev and informed him of China's reform and open-up 
policy. 
  In the over-two-hour-long meeting, Li briefed Nazarbayev on 
China' reform and open policy as well as its efforts to build up 
a socialist market economy. 
  Nazarbayev said that his country is also exploring the path 
of reform and hopes to learn from China's practice in this 
regard. 
  Earlier today, Li Peng held talks with Prime Minister S. A. 
Tereshchenko of Kazakhstan on ways to strengthen bilateral trade 
and economic cooperation, particularly measures to improve 
transportation between the two countries. 

