<H3> <TI>   Li Meets President, Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Meets President, Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804002294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1527 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2804002294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Sun Zhanlin (1327 0594 2651) and Hu Xiaoguang </F>
(5170 2556 0342)] 
  [Text] Almaty, 27 Apr (XINHUA) -- Visiting Chinese Premier 
Li Peng met again with Kazakh President Nazarbayev this 
afternoon. 
  As requested during the two-and-a-half-hour meeting, Premier 
Li Peng briefed the Kazakh president on China's major policies 
and measures in economic reform and efforts in establishing a 
socialist market economic system. Showing great interest in Li 
Peng's briefings, Nazarbayev said that his country is also 
exploring the path of reform and would like to have a thorough 
understanding of the conditions of China's reform and opening 
up. He suggested mutual visits between officials and experts of 
the economic departments of the two countries. 
  Earlier today, Premier Li Peng held talks with Kazakh Prime 
Minister Tereshchenko on ways to further strengthen economic 
cooperation and bilateral trade. They also exchanged views on 
improving communications and transport conditions between the 
two nations. Kazakh officials in charge of economics, trade, 
energy, and communications departments also attended the meeting 
and expressed their views on cooperation in their respective 
fields. 

</TEXT>

