<H3> <TI>   Japan's Socialists Quit Ruling Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's Socialists Quit Ruling Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604001894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1710 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604001894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Japan's socialists quit 
the ruling coalition on Tuesday [26 April], NHK Public 
Television said. 
  The socialists' move is plunging Prime Minister Tsutomu 
Hata's government into crisis just hours after they helped to 
elect him. 
  Hata is expected to form his new cabinet on Monday after 
winning a parliamentary vote earlier in the day. 

</TEXT>

