<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Invites IAEA To Inspect Nuclear Facility </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Invites IAEA To Inspect Nuclear Facility </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804063994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0609 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804063994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (XINHUA) -- The Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) has invited inspectors from 
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) to observe the 
replacement of fuel rods at the Yongbyon reactor, a DPRK Foreign 
Ministry spokesman said today. 
  The spokesman told reporters that the DPRK would fully 
guarantee access for the inspectors and turn over the replaced 
fuel rods to the IAEA for examination to ensure the continuity 
of nuclear safety. 
  The spokesman also said he hopes the United States and the 
IAEA would respect DPRK's status regarding the nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty and adopt just standpoints and attitudes. 
  He added if the United States and the IAEA impose the 
further 
inspections,the situation will become more complicated. 
  The IAEA has said it will observe the replacement of fuel 
rods during this "additional inspection", reports said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

